rComments: Professor Holland is fantastic. Coming from a non-literature background, I was pleasantly surprised at how easy she made the course to understand. She is very knowledgeable and dives into each work with intensity and depth. Needless to say, you have to read a lot of material in this course, but she makes it worthwhile with her insightful lectures.
I'm quite unfamiliar to writing literature papers, but I still managed to do decent in the class. She seems very nice and is very passionate about the subject.

Very interesting lectures, she is clearly passionate about the content and ready to make you passionate about it. READING HEAVY. Dont take this class if you wont have time to do the readings. Pop quizzes! (Theyre usually every other week though). Very good course, glad I took it but decided to CR/NCR because of tough grading. Tests are online!
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Lots of reading, but very knowledgeable about the material. I found her lectures interesting, and she explains concepts clearly and precisely. Though, if you find yourself confused, she'll readily clarify it in lecture or office hours. Have taken a few of her classes and grading is consistent and fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: The lectures were extremely dry and surface level. It seemed like there was no emotion or investment in the material from the professor. She somehow managed to make one of the most incredible literary figures of all time seem quite dry in her lectures, mainly due to a large amount of direct reading of her own papers in a monotone voice.

took her chekhov class. lots of reading, and there were 5 pop quizzes throughout the term so you had to make sure to read it all. they aren't in depth at all though so as long as you've read what was assigned you're fine. papers aren't too hard and you have a lot of leeway with them. not amazing as a lecturer, but interesting enough.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']
